The article emphasizes the importance of the right to vote in the United States. It states that voting is central to the nation's identity and serves as the foundation of liberty. The article acknowledges the sacrifices and efforts of civil rights leaders in expanding voting access, but also highlights the ongoing challenges and attempts to restrict Americans' access to the ballot. The author calls on all eligible Americans to register to vote, encourages policymakers to defend and strengthen voting rights, and proclaims September 28, 2021, as National Voter Registration Day.